    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="312"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">548.D1/208: Circular instruction</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">American Diplomatic Representatives in South America</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="66" xml:id="d312fn66">Also sent to the Consular Officer at
                        Guayaquil.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-12">February 12,
                            1935</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sirs</hi>: The Department has been informed by High
                    Commissioner James G. McDonald, representing the High Commission for Refugees
                    (Jewish and others) Coming from Germany, and Mr. Samuel Guy Inman, that they are
                    about to visit various countries of South America listed in the enclosed
                    itinerary to treat with them concerning the entrance of some of the refugees
                    into those countries.</p>
                <p>You will please extend appropriate courtesies to these gentlemen, bearing in
                    mind, however, that they do not represent the United States. There is enclosed
                    for your information a memorandum<note n="67" xml:id="d312fn67">Not
                        printed.</note> concerning the High Commission and this Government’s
                    relation to it.</p>
                <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">William Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
